# Tabular Listing Component Standard

When creating or refactoring tabular listing components, follow these patterns.

## Reference Implementation
- **With Tabs**: `src/app/modules/report/chat-interaction`
- **List Component**: `src/app/modules/report/chat-interaction/components/live_chat_agent_list`

## Required Imports
```typescript
import { Pagination } from '@bmp/components/table/pagination.model';
import { DEFAULT_PAGINATION_CONFIG } from 'app/modules/report/chat-interaction/shared/const/live_chat_agent.const';
```

## Required Properties
```typescript
public items: any[] = [];
public pagination: Pagination = { ...DEFAULT_PAGINATION_CONFIG };
public isLoading = false;
public isSearching = false;
private destroy$ = new Subject<void>();
private searchSubject$ = new Subject<string>();
```

## Search Debounce Pattern (REQUIRED)
Always use 300ms debounce on search:
```typescript
ngOnInit() {
    this.searchSubject$.pipe(debounceTime(300), distinctUntilChanged(), takeUntil(this.destroy$))
        .subscribe(term => { this.requestParams.filter = term; this.resetPagination(); this.loadData(); });
    this.loadData();
}
updateSearch(term: string) { this.isSearching = !!term; this.searchSubject$.next(term); }
clearSearch() { this.isSearching = false; this.requestParams.filter = ''; this.resetPagination(); this.loadData(); }
```

## Pagination Pattern (REQUIRED)
```typescript
private resetPagination() {
    this.pagination.pageNo = DEFAULT_PAGINATION_CONFIG.pageNo;
    this.pagination.pageSize = DEFAULT_PAGINATION_CONFIG.pageSize;
}
onPageChange(event: { pageNo: number; pageSize: number }) {
    this.pagination.pageNo = event.pageNo;
    this.pagination.pageSize = event.pageSize;
    this.loadData();
}
```

## Load Data Pattern (REQUIRED)
```typescript
loadData() {
    this.isLoading = true; this.cdr.markForCheck();
    this.requestParams.pageNo = this.pagination.pageNo;
    this.requestParams.pageSize = this.pagination.pageSize;
    this.apiService.getData(this.requestParams).pipe(
        takeUntil(this.destroy$),
        finalize(() => { this.isLoading = false; this.cdr.markForCheck(); })
    ).subscribe({ next: res => this.handleResponse(res), error: err => console.error(err) });
}
```

## Handle Response Pattern (CRITICAL)
NEVER overwrite pageNo from API response:
```typescript
handleResponse(res) {
    this.items = (res.data || []).map(item => ({ ...item, actionConfig: this.actionConfig }));
    this.pagination.totalItems = res.totalRecord || 0;  // ONLY update totalItems
    this.cdr.markForCheck();
}
```

## SCSS Pattern
Use `report-list` class with `margin-top` (NOT padding-top):
```scss
.report-list {
    margin-top: $spacing-24;
    .row { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; gap: $spacing-16-new; align-items: center; }
    .row-end { display: flex; gap: $spacing-16-new; }
    .hidden { display: none; }
    ::ng-deep .table-container { margin-top: $spacing-24 !important; }
}
```

## With Tabs vs Without Tabs
- **With tabs**: Put ScrollbarDirective and DynamicHeightDirective in PARENT component only
- **Without tabs**: Put ScrollbarDirective and DynamicHeightDirective in the page itself

## DO:
- Use `DEFAULT_PAGINATION_CONFIG` and `Pagination` type
- 300ms debounce on search
- `resetPagination()` before `loadData()` when filters change
- Read from `this.pagination` in `loadData()`
- Only update `totalItems` in response handler
- `takeUntil(this.destroy$)` and `cdr.markForCheck()`

## DON'T:
- Pass page as parameter: `loadData(page: number)`
- Overwrite `pagination.pageNo` from API response
- Make API calls on every keystroke
- Use `padding-top` or `height: 100%` in list SCSS
